      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the buildup of hydrogen ions is the primary culprit for that burning sensation, making it an unavoidable part of high-intensity training. You can't completely stop it during maximal effort sprints, but you can manage it by ensuring proper recovery between sets, which allows your body time to clear some of the byproducts. It generally takes anywhere from a few minutes to a couple of hours for your body to fully buffer and clear the accumulated metabolic waste, depending on the intensity of the workout.",
